hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I have my own business my foldaway mirror double offer If Noel Fielding had said to me, on the first day of university, as he sat down next to me looking like a slightly wonky Evan Dando crossed with the love child of David Ginola and Bruce Forsyth: “Hey, I’m Noel, nice to meet you - in the next 20 years we’ll take the Edinburgh Fringe by storm, sell out Brixton Academy for a record seven nights, hang out with heroes like Tim Burgess, Gary Numan and the Beastie Boys, headline our own festival, play at the Roxy in LA in front of a very excited Robin Williams, sell out Wembley and the O2 Arena, create a bestselling book, record an album at Jimi Hendrix’s Electric Ladyland Studios in New York, have a member of Led Zeppelin tell us ‘You Rock!’, and spend the best part of a year touring the country having the time of our lives, partying with our mates on a tour bus bigger than this classroom,” I would probably have deemed him a complete and utter fruitloop and gone and sat somewhere else.
